What is constructor Overloading:

Constructor overloading is used when we need same constructor with different parameters. Constructors are executed when the object is initialized.
In the below example we have constructor with same names and different parameters.

We are using parameterized constructor Below.

Sample program:


package selenium;

public class Constructor_overloading {

	Constructor_overloading(int a, int b) {

		int sum = a + b;

		System.out.println("The first constructor loading.." + sum);

	}

	Constructor_overloading(int i, int j, int k) {

		int sum = i + j + k;

		System.out.println("The second constructor loading.." + sum);

	}

	public static void main(String[] Args) {
		Constructor_overloading object = new Constructor_overloading(5, 5);
		Constructor_overloading object1 = new Constructor_overloading(5, 5, 5);

	}

}
